1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO TECHNOLOGY; EXPANDING THE DEPARTMENT OF
3 INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY'S EQUIPMENT REPLACEMENT PLANS TO
4 INCLUDE SOFTWARE; RENAMING THE EQUIPMENT REPLACEMENT
5 REVOLVING FUNDS AS THE EQUIPMENT AND SOFTWARE REPLACEMENT
6 REVOLVING FUNDS.
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
9 SECTION 1. Section 9-27-11 NMSA 1978 (being Laws 2008,
10 Chapter 84, Section 2, as amended) is amended to read:
11 "9-27-11. EQUIPMENT AND SOFTWARE REPLACEMENT PLANS--
12 EQUIPMENT AND SOFTWARE REPLACEMENT REVOLVING FUNDS.--
13 A. In order to plan for the expenditure of capital
14 investments necessary to provide goods and services to the
15 state and its agencies and to local public bodies and other
16 enterprise customers, the department shall establish and
17 maintain an equipment and software replacement plan for each
18 of the department's enterprise functions. No later than
19 September 1 of each year, the plans shall be submitted to the
20 department of finance and administration and the legislature,
21 accompanied by a reconciliation report of the preceding
22 fiscal year reflecting financial activity in each of the
23 equipment and software replacement revolving funds
24 established pursuant to this section.
25 B. Upon the request of the secretary, the state SRC/SB 132
Page 1

1 treasurer shall establish in the state treasury such
2 "equipment and software replacement revolving funds" as are
3 necessary to administer each of the department's enterprise
4 functions. The revolving funds shall consist of legislative
5 appropriations to the funds and transfers made to the funds
6 pursuant to Subsection C of this section. Income from
7 investment of the revolving funds shall be credited back to
8 the funds, and money in the funds shall not revert at the end
9 of a fiscal year. Expenditures from the funds shall only be
10 made pursuant to an appropriation from the legislature and
11 only for the purpose of acquiring and replacing capital
12 equipment and software used to provide enterprise services
13 pursuant to the department's equipment and software
14 replacement plans.
15 C. The department shall record amounts due to the
16 equipment and software replacement revolving funds each fiscal
17 year, based on the calculation of amortization and
depreciation applicable to each enterprise service as
18
reflected in the department's published cost structures for
19
calculation of rates for services. Transfers to the funds
20
shall be made from the operating funds of each enterprise in
21
amounts that reconcile with the recorded amounts due. The
22
recording of amounts due to the equipment and software
23
replacement revolving funds and the transfer of the funds
24
shall be consistent with generally accepted accounting
